ghRes_the-all-new-bmw-m4-c.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MzIx/P90548548_highRes_the-all-new-bmw-m4-c.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3MzIx/P90548548_highRes_the-all-new-bmw-m4-c.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-cybertruck-will-hurt-your-wallet-a-little-more\"\u003eThe Cybertruck will hurt your wallet a little more\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eOn the other side of the coin, the Tesla Cybertruck is available from $79,990 and comes in All-Wheel Drive and Cyberbeast trim levels. The base model features a range of up to 325 miles, while the Cyberbeast will run you just shy of $100,000 and offers a range of 320 miles.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Tesla Cybertruck\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2160\" height=\"1440\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTMwNTI1Mjk5MDU4Mjg4/tesla-cybertruck-2.png\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eWhen it comes to performance, the base Cybertruck All-Wheel Drive rolls out with dual electric motors that generate 600 horsepower and 525 lb-ft of torque. The Cyberbeast gets a third electric motor that increases performance to 845 horsepower and 863 lb-ft of torque. In its quickest form, the Cybertruck races to 60 mph in 2.6 seconds.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"which-truck-is-better-at-being-a-truck\"\u003eWhich truck is better at being a truck?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eWhen it comes to aesthetics, the Rivian R1T definitely looks more like a truck, thanks to its more traditional design. The electric pickup is capable of towing up to 11,000 lbs. when properly equipped. Payload capacity is pretty fair, coming in at 2,161 lbs. The cargo bed measures 54 inches in length and 51.1 inches in width. The R1T also has a maximum ground clearance of 14.6 inches.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Rivian R1T\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1965\" height=\"1104\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjA5MTIyNzIxMDc0NDU2NDIw/rivian-r1t-reveal-707948.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eDon’t count the Cybertruck out, though. While it might look a little odd, Tesla’s truck matches the R1T with an 11,000-lbs. towing capacity, regardless of trim level. It tops Rivian’s truck as well, with the capability to haul up to 2,500 lbs. in its six-by-four foot cargo bed. The Cybertruck features an active air suspension at both axles that allows for up to 17.4 inches of ground clearance, too.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe Tesla Cybertruck looks great on paper, but it’s been marred by manufacturing defects, political factors, and its polarizing design. The Rivian R1T is a solid truck by spec sheet alone, and it certainly fits the part with pretty standard pickup styling. With CEO Elon Musk’s political leanings putting the entire Tesla brand in jeopardy, the Cybertruck’s future looks bleak. The time for Rivian to strike is now, and with the right moves, the EV manufacturer could see its market share increase in 2025.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n            \n        \n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Genesis X Gran Coupe and X Gran Convertible concepts\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 80px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genesisxgrancoupeconceptxgranconvertibleconceptmakeworldpremiereatseoulmobilityshow2025-6.png 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg3Mjky/250403-genes